{"lemma":"ثَنْيَةٌ","slug":"ثَنْيَةٌ","root":"ث.ن.#","root_slug":"ث-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4763","n4764","n4773"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"duplicature, tuck, pleat, fold, twist"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dale, mountain pass"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fold, crease, plait"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inward side, inside"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"incisor, any of front teeth"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4763","headword_ar":"ثُنْيَةٌ","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vunoyaA","text_ar":"ثُنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4764","headword_ar":"ثِنْيَةٌ","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, most ignoble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meanest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the people of his house; applied to a man. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vunoyaAnN","text_ar":"ثُنْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4773","headword_ar":"ثَنِيَّةٌ","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqabapN","text_ar":"عَقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, M, Mgh, K:) or the latter means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long mountain that lies across the road, and which the road traverses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any such mountain that is traversed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) so called because it lies before the road, and crosses it; or because it turns away him who traverses it: (Mgh:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqabap","text_ar":"عَقَبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S; and so in copies of the K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a high road of what is thus termed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K accord. to the TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, a mountain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like that which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqobN","text_ar":"نَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road to a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a part of a mountain that requires one, in traversing it, to ascend and descend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it turned the course of journeying: (Er-Rághib, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanaAyaA","text_ar":"ثَنَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S:) which signifies also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such roads as are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaArij","text_ar":"مَدَارِج"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T.) Hence the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tal~aAEu Alv~anaAyaA","text_ar":"طَلَّاعُ الثَّنَايَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one rises to eminences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to lofty things"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the means of attaining such things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tal~aAEu A^anojudK","text_ar":"طَلَّاعُ اَنْجُدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S:) or, like the latter phrase,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is accustomed to embark in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to surmount,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master, lofty and difficult things:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is hardy, strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy; one who embarks in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertakes, great affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See an ex. under the heading of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu jalaA","text_ar":"اِبْنُ جَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jlw","text_ar":"جلو"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TlE","text_ar":"طلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  Also, (T, S, M, &c.,) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanaAyaA","text_ar":"ثَنَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaniy~aAtN","text_ar":"ثَنِيَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of certain teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the foremost in the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) [namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the central incisors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four in number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, Msb,) to man, and to the camel, (T, M, &c.,) and to the wild beast, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the fore part of the mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two above and two below:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, K:) so called as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaniy~ap","text_ar":"ثَنِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a mountain, in form and hardness; (TA;) or because each of them is placed next to its fellow. (Mgh.)       -A2-  Also fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaniY~N","text_ar":"ثَنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (T, S, M, &c.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vunoyaA","text_ar":"ثُنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places."}],"source_refs":["AA","M","Mgh","K","T","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AB%D9%86%D9%8A%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"ثنيةُ المذَابِيح","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_52","lexicon_en":"Yāqūt al-Ḥamawī, Muʿjam al-Buldān (d. 1229)","lexicon_ar":"معجم البلدان لياقوت الحموي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=138962#be41fc","body_html":"ثنيةُ المذَابِيح:<br>كأنه جمع مذبوح: جبل ثهلان، وفيها قصبة لحيان الكلابي وصاحب له."}]}}